The paper discusses model-based security testing (MBST), which involves the use of models to specify and generate security test cases. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with the systematic and efficient specification and documentation of security test objectives, test cases, and test suites. Additionally, the paper focuses on security properties such as confidentiality, integrity, authentication, authorization, availability, and non-repudiation, which are related to computer security (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the usage of security test patterns, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the automated or semi-automated generation of test cases.
